                            <comment id="17866979" author="chia7712" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 11:15:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pardon me, do you mean `junit-platform.properties` file is included in the kafka-clients.jar? if so, I don&apos;t notice the file in kafka-clients-3.7.1.jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17866981" author="awilkinson" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 11:23:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not quite. It&apos;s in the test-classified jars:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/kafka/kafka-clients/3.7.1/kafka-clients-3.7.1-test.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/kafka/kafka-clients/3.7.1/kafka-clients-3.7.1-test.jar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/kafka/kafka-server-common/3.7.1/kafka-server-common-3.7.1-test.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/kafka/kafka-server-common/3.7.1/kafka-server-common-3.7.1-test.jar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17866982" author="chia7712" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 11:33:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks for confirmation. You are right that the junit file should be excluded. We will fix it. For another, why putting those test jars into classpath? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17866983" author="chia7712" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 11:34:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to exclude the file, we can simply add &quot;exclude &quot;junit-platform.properties&quot;&quot; to the testJar task (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/build.gradle#L586&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/build.gradle#L586&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17866996" author="JIRAUSER306086" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 11:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi&#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=awilkinson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;awilkinson&quot;&gt;awilkinson&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chia7712&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chia7712&quot;&gt;chia7712&lt;/a&gt;&#160; , I&apos;d Like to look into this. Can you assign this to me?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17867000" author="awilkinson" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2024 12:33:28 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are right that the junit file should be excluded. We will fix it&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For another, why putting those test jars into classpath?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They contain utility code that&apos;s useful when testing applications that use Kafka. For example, Spring for Apache Kafka uses &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.kafka.test.TestUtils&lt;/tt&gt; from kafka-clients-3.7.1-test.jar in its testing support.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17867147" author="chia7712" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2024 01:50:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=awilkinson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;awilkinson&quot;&gt;awilkinson&lt;/a&gt; Could you please take a look at PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/16624&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/16624&lt;/a&gt; ? it would be great to get your confirmation &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
